Dear all,

IIT Madras Aquatics team put up an excellent performance in the Inter IIT
Aquatics meet bagging a total of 7 Gold medals, 7 Silver medals and 4
Bronze medals in Swimming events finishing first in both Men's and Women's
Championship. We also placed fourth in Water Polo (Men).

Currently, IIT Madras is placed first in all the three championships,
namely Men's GC, Women's GC and Overall Championship. The table is as
follows:



*First *

*Second*

*Third*

*Fourth*

*Men's GC*

Madras and Kgp (12)

Bombay (10)

Kanpur (6)

Delhi (4)

*Women's GC*

Madras (10)

Delhi (6)

Kgp (4)

Bombay (2)

*Overall Championship*

Madras (22)

Kgp (16)

Bombay (12)

Delhi (10)

Highlights of the meet:

1. *CK* *Anand Krishnan - *3 Gold medals with a new meet record in 50m
Freestyle was awarded the Best Swimmer (Men)

2. *Kamala Devi L R* - 1 Gold and 2 Silver medals, narrowly missing out on
the Best Swimmer Award (Women)

3. *Anuj Sindgi *(Freshie) - 2 Silver and 1 Bronze medal

4. IIT Madras broke the 4x100m Freestyle Relay record by 3 seconds. We now
hold 12 out of the 16 records in Men's Swimming events


We thank everyone for your support! Go Madras!

Best regards,
